question.title: Gradle lockfiles contain excess entries
question.body:
Observed using Gradle 8.7

When I update my lockfiles using

./gradlew resolveAndLockAll --write-locks

I sometimes find a number of entries that are present but when I check the dependencies they are not there. When I delete the lockfile and regenerate it, I get a very different (and more correct) lockfile without these "excess" entries.

Expectation: Updating the lockfile and regenerating it from scratch should result in the same output.
